1
00:00:01,930 --> 00:00:03,130
You said you regretted it.

2
00:00:03,800 --> 00:00:05,870
You regretted meeting me
and ruining your life.

3
00:00:08,440 --> 00:00:10,440
I let you go, so you can live a good life.

4
00:00:11,010 --> 00:00:12,740
I didn't ask you to stay.

5
00:00:15,180 --> 00:00:16,170
But...

6
00:00:17,710 --> 00:00:18,710
But

7
00:00:21,050 --> 00:00:22,850
why are you here again?

8
00:00:26,250 --> 00:00:28,520
Whenever you stayed by my side,

9
00:00:30,260 --> 00:00:32,030
do you know what went through my head?

10
00:00:35,460 --> 00:00:36,500
"I miss you."

11
00:00:40,530 --> 00:00:43,070
"I miss you, Hong Dae-young."

12
00:00:54,750 --> 00:00:56,120
I missed you too.

13
00:02:07,690 --> 00:02:09,820
You look just like when you were young.

14
00:02:12,190 --> 00:02:13,590
How did I miss it?

15
00:02:16,520 --> 00:02:17,830
Come to think of it,

16
00:02:18,930 --> 00:02:20,770
so many things didn't make sense.

17
00:02:23,140 --> 00:02:24,740
I must be a fool.

18
00:02:26,140 --> 00:02:27,210
No.

19
00:02:28,380 --> 00:02:29,740
I was wrong.

20
00:02:32,510 --> 00:02:35,180
I should've told you the truth.

21
00:02:37,420 --> 00:02:38,550
I'm sorry.

22
00:02:52,270 --> 00:02:57,070
=Episode 15, Confession=

23
00:03:01,610 --> 00:03:02,680
What?

24
00:03:02,880 --> 00:03:05,080
You thought I was having an affair?

25
00:03:06,610 --> 00:03:07,720
It's because

26
00:03:08,880 --> 00:03:11,250
I didn't know why you wanted a divorce.

27
00:03:12,690 --> 00:03:16,690
Is that why you were so mean to me in the beginning?

28
00:03:18,560 --> 00:03:19,590
Yes.

29
00:03:20,190 --> 00:03:21,230
I'm sorry.

30
00:03:23,200 --> 00:03:24,200
It's okay.

31
00:03:25,020 --> 00:03:26,500
It was just a misunderstanding.

32
00:03:26,670 --> 00:03:28,300
Now I know

33
00:03:28,470 --> 00:03:30,910
that even if you're a married couple,

34
00:03:31,240 --> 00:03:32,970
you can't know what the other is thinking

35
00:03:33,870 --> 00:03:35,040
if they don't say anything.

36
00:03:36,540 --> 00:03:38,310
Thank you for understanding.

37
00:03:40,050 --> 00:03:40,980
Oh, right.

38
00:03:42,180 --> 00:03:43,620
There's one more thing.

39
00:03:44,190 --> 00:03:46,790
I'm telling you so that
there won't be any misunderstandings.

40
00:03:47,390 --> 00:03:50,190
There's nothing going on
between me and Mr. Ye Ji-hoon.

41
00:03:51,790 --> 00:03:53,390
At that time, I--

42
00:03:53,460 --> 00:03:55,330
You must've had a really hard time.

43
00:03:55,500 --> 00:03:57,400
You had to lie because of me.

44
00:03:57,930 --> 00:03:58,900
I'm sorry.

45
00:04:00,590 --> 00:04:01,700
It's okay.

46
00:04:02,400 --> 00:04:03,740
Thank you

47
00:04:04,710 --> 00:04:07,580
for taking care of us without our knowing.

48
00:04:13,410 --> 00:04:15,320
Oh, the bus is here.

49
00:04:16,580 --> 00:04:18,390
- I'll get going now.
- Right.

50
00:04:19,920 --> 00:04:21,060
Get home safe.

51
00:04:46,880 --> 00:04:47,820
What?

52
00:04:48,650 --> 00:04:50,050
Why did you get on?

53
00:04:51,320 --> 00:04:52,520
Let's not

54
00:04:54,120 --> 00:04:55,560
go home today.

55
00:04:56,720 --> 00:04:57,790
What?

56
00:05:19,510 --> 00:05:21,080
- 1, 2.
- I said it was dangerous.

57
00:05:22,720 --> 00:05:24,420
My goodness.

58
00:05:57,990 --> 00:05:59,550
Oh, Mom.

59
00:05:59,720 --> 00:06:00,890
Are you just getting in?

60
00:06:00,960 --> 00:06:03,360
What? Yes.

61
00:06:03,790 --> 00:06:06,660
I had plans, and I came home a bit late.

62
00:06:06,830 --> 00:06:08,600
You weren't a bit late.

63
00:06:09,460 --> 00:06:10,560
Right.

64
00:06:12,470 --> 00:06:13,470
It's okay.

65
00:06:13,870 --> 00:06:16,140
You need to release your stress too.

66
00:06:16,600 --> 00:06:17,640
What?

67
00:06:19,770 --> 00:06:21,940
Wait a bit. I'll make you breakfast.

68
00:06:22,100 --> 00:06:25,010
No, it's okay. You must be tired.
Get some rest.

69
00:06:25,380 --> 00:06:27,600
It's fine. Just wait a bit.

70
00:06:38,330 --> 00:06:41,200
Back in the days, I would be fine
after playing all night long.

71
00:06:41,260 --> 00:06:43,430
But it's not easy now that I'm older.

72
00:06:50,270 --> 00:06:52,170
Hey. What is it?

73
00:06:53,340 --> 00:06:55,880
Nothing. I just wanted to hear your voice.

74
00:06:55,940 --> 00:06:56,980
What?

75
00:06:58,910 --> 00:07:00,750
We just said goodbye.

76
00:07:05,150 --> 00:07:07,490
Who is she on the phone with at this hour?

77
00:07:12,490 --> 00:07:13,530
Hong Si-a.

78
00:07:17,200 --> 00:07:18,870
- Are you going to class?
- Yes.

79
00:07:19,870 --> 00:07:21,000
Let's go together.

80
00:07:21,700 --> 00:07:24,240
What if someone sees us?

81
00:07:24,570 --> 00:07:26,510
I told you to keep it a secret in school.

82
00:07:27,440 --> 00:07:29,240
I don't care if we get caught.

83
00:07:29,780 --> 00:07:31,450
Do you care?

84
00:07:33,250 --> 00:07:35,520
No. It's not like that.

85
00:07:42,960 --> 00:07:43,960
What is it?

86
00:07:44,790 --> 00:07:45,860
What's wrong?

87
00:07:47,530 --> 00:07:50,130
Si-a. You came to school early today.

88
00:07:51,170 --> 00:07:53,300
What is it?
Why are you picking a fight with me?

89
00:07:54,330 --> 00:07:55,540
I'm complimenting you.

90
00:07:56,670 --> 00:07:59,240
You're not late for school these days,
and you're very diligent.

91
00:08:02,010 --> 00:08:04,480
(- Hooray!
- Go!)

92
00:08:04,550 --> 00:08:06,650
(- Go!
- Let's go!)

93
00:08:06,710 --> 00:08:09,050
(- Go!
- Go!)

94
00:08:09,120 --> 00:08:11,820
(You did well, okay?
Who gave you such fast and strong legs?)

95
00:08:17,480 --> 00:08:18,560
What are you talking about?

96
00:08:20,060 --> 00:08:21,100
My goodness.

97
00:08:28,070 --> 00:08:29,940
What am I thinking right now?

98
00:08:43,420 --> 00:08:45,750
Please take a look
at these lucky bracelets.

99
00:08:48,120 --> 00:08:49,190
Take a look at them.

100
00:08:54,160 --> 00:08:55,360
This is pretty.

101
00:08:56,230 --> 00:08:57,500
Can I pay with a card?

102
00:08:57,560 --> 00:09:00,030
We only accept cash here.

103
00:09:00,870 --> 00:09:02,040
Is that so?

104
00:09:03,240 --> 00:09:05,240
- I'll come back another time.
- Okay.

105
00:09:10,710 --> 00:09:13,210
Oh, aren't you the baseball player,
Ye Ji-hoon?

106
00:09:13,350 --> 00:09:16,020
I'm a fan. Can you give me your autograph?

107
00:09:16,850 --> 00:09:17,920
Sure.

108
00:09:19,150 --> 00:09:22,060
In return, can you do me a favor?

109
00:09:23,560 --> 00:09:25,490
Anchorwoman Jung Da-jung.

110
00:09:26,790 --> 00:09:28,900
What? Hello.

111
00:09:28,960 --> 00:09:31,470
I'm a fan. Here.

112
00:09:37,040 --> 00:09:38,370
What is this?

113
00:09:38,440 --> 00:09:41,180
It's a present. Goodbye.

114
00:09:41,240 --> 00:09:42,410
Hey.

115
00:09:46,950 --> 00:09:48,850
I was going to give it to Si-a.

116
00:09:50,650 --> 00:09:52,090
I guess I should wear it.

117
00:10:08,140 --> 00:10:11,610
Do you remember the car accident

118
00:10:12,670 --> 00:10:14,010
that occurred on Christmas Day?

119
00:10:17,440 --> 00:10:19,050
Why did you do that?

120
00:10:23,580 --> 00:10:24,720
I'm sorry.

121
00:10:37,130 --> 00:10:39,830
(Hiring New and Experienced
Anchors and Sports Reporters)

122
00:10:45,570 --> 00:10:46,740
Hello, Dae-young.

123
00:10:47,240 --> 00:10:48,610
What were you doing?

124
00:10:48,780 --> 00:10:50,880
I was looking at places to interview with.

125
00:10:51,180 --> 00:10:53,250
(- Interview?)
- Yes.

126
00:10:53,310 --> 00:10:54,780
I'm going to apply to everywhere I can.

127
00:10:54,850 --> 00:10:56,150
(Goodness.)

128
00:10:56,220 --> 00:10:59,550
I'm sure a lot of broadcasting stations
will be fighting to hire you.

129
00:10:59,620 --> 00:11:00,750
My gosh.

130
00:11:01,590 --> 00:11:03,790
What about you? What were you doing?

131
00:11:04,660 --> 00:11:07,090
I just finished practice,
and I'm on my way home.

132
00:11:07,560 --> 00:11:11,160
You had practice today?
Were you okay after staying up all night?

133
00:11:11,230 --> 00:11:12,930
Of course. I'm fine.

134
00:11:14,430 --> 00:11:16,500
Being young is nice.

135
00:11:16,570 --> 00:11:18,670
I woke up when the sun set.

136
00:11:18,740 --> 00:11:20,810
(It's good to get plenty of rest.)

137
00:11:21,640 --> 00:11:22,710
Da-jung.

138
00:11:24,710 --> 00:11:26,010
Are you free tomorrow?

139
00:11:26,350 --> 00:11:27,380
Tomorrow?

140
00:11:28,350 --> 00:11:31,220
Yes, I'm free. Why?

141
00:11:33,750 --> 00:11:36,790
Let's go on a date.

142
00:11:37,660 --> 00:11:40,160
Gosh. A date?

143
00:11:40,230 --> 00:11:41,190
Yes.

144
00:11:41,760 --> 00:11:43,260
Is there anything you want to do?

145
00:11:44,230 --> 00:11:46,370
Yes, there is.

146
00:11:56,040 --> 00:11:59,610
What is it?
Why did the two of you call us here?

147
00:12:00,210 --> 00:12:02,680
Right. You said
you had something urgent to tell us.

148
00:12:04,520 --> 00:12:05,590
Deok-jin.

149
00:12:06,320 --> 00:12:07,790
You're my friend,

150
00:12:07,850 --> 00:12:10,320
and Woo-young is your son.

151
00:12:10,460 --> 00:12:12,260
That's why I tried to hold it in.

152
00:12:13,660 --> 00:12:14,730
But

153
00:12:16,360 --> 00:12:18,070
I can't hold it in any longer.

154
00:12:18,700 --> 00:12:19,730
Hold what in?

155
00:12:25,810 --> 00:12:28,010
I'm sure now.

156
00:12:28,480 --> 00:12:29,480
Actually,

157
00:12:30,140 --> 00:12:31,410
I sincerely

158
00:12:33,650 --> 00:12:34,880
love Woo-young.

159
00:12:35,480 --> 00:12:36,550
- What?
- What?

160
00:12:37,880 --> 00:12:40,020
Woo-young is turning legal soon.

161
00:12:40,590 --> 00:12:43,520
In Hollywood, an 18-year-old age gap
is considered nothing.

162
00:12:43,590 --> 00:12:44,690
So, Deok-jin,

163
00:12:45,630 --> 00:12:46,660
give us your blessing.

164
00:12:50,400 --> 00:12:51,400
Well,

165
00:12:52,500 --> 00:12:54,740
I can't really say anything.

166
00:12:58,240 --> 00:12:59,740
I can't hold it in anymore.

167
00:13:00,140 --> 00:13:02,640
Da-jung, he's actually Hong Dae-young.

168
00:13:02,710 --> 00:13:04,480
You really can't do this!

169
00:13:04,540 --> 00:13:06,310
What are you saying?

170
00:13:06,580 --> 00:13:09,220
Deok-jin, I'll take it that you're
approving of this.

171
00:13:09,580 --> 00:13:12,920
Woo-young and I are official from now on,

172
00:13:12,990 --> 00:13:14,920
so Ae-rin, keep that in mind.

173
00:13:17,590 --> 00:13:18,860
We'll get going first.

174
00:13:19,530 --> 00:13:21,260
Hey!

175
00:13:22,200 --> 00:13:24,160
How come all of Mr. Go's friends

176
00:13:24,530 --> 00:13:26,170
are so weird?

177
00:13:26,470 --> 00:13:28,100
Maybe I should quit.

178
00:13:29,670 --> 00:13:31,240
Da-jung! No.

179
00:13:31,300 --> 00:13:32,370
What...

180
00:13:39,910 --> 00:13:41,620
(I'm not entirely happy that you all lied to me,)

181
00:13:41,680 --> 00:13:44,480
(but still, thanks for helping Dae-young all along.)

182
00:13:44,580 --> 00:13:45,650
What is she saying?

183
00:13:46,290 --> 00:13:47,290
What?

184
00:13:48,090 --> 00:13:51,360
Did they fool us just now?

185
00:13:54,260 --> 00:13:55,800
My gosh.

186
00:14:03,140 --> 00:14:05,470
We have some really great friends.

187
00:14:05,770 --> 00:14:06,770
Yes, we do.

188
00:14:09,310 --> 00:14:11,680
That's...

189
00:14:12,250 --> 00:14:15,520
Yes, it's the necklace that you gave me.

190
00:14:20,320 --> 00:14:21,320
It's beautiful.

191
00:14:23,720 --> 00:14:24,790
Where are we going now?

192
00:14:24,860 --> 00:14:26,290
Hold on.

193
00:14:27,160 --> 00:14:28,260
Here.

194
00:14:30,800 --> 00:14:32,930
What's with the car?

195
00:14:33,330 --> 00:14:34,670
I borrowed it from Deok-jin.

196
00:14:34,870 --> 00:14:36,800
I wanted to go somewhere nice.
It's our first date in a long while.

197
00:14:36,870 --> 00:14:39,740
No! You're still a minor.

198
00:14:39,810 --> 00:14:40,940
Come on.

199
00:14:41,110 --> 00:14:44,410
You know that I'm a great driver.

200
00:14:44,680 --> 00:14:46,080
Still, no.

201
00:14:46,150 --> 00:14:48,980
If we get into an accident,
you'll get caught without a license.

202
00:14:50,580 --> 00:14:51,590
Is that right?

203
00:14:51,820 --> 00:14:53,290
What should we do then?

204
00:14:53,620 --> 00:14:55,220
I've already planned the date out.

205
00:14:55,960 --> 00:14:59,360
Then leave the driving to me today.

206
00:14:59,990 --> 00:15:02,960
I've driven without getting
into an accident for ten years.

207
00:15:13,470 --> 00:15:15,940
Don't you think you're going
a little too fast?

208
00:15:16,280 --> 00:15:19,010
What's wrong?
I'm still under the speed limit.

209
00:15:20,350 --> 00:15:21,350
Do you

210
00:15:22,220 --> 00:15:23,280
not trust me?

211
00:15:23,550 --> 00:15:24,950
Of course I do.

212
00:15:25,350 --> 00:15:26,990
I've just never seen you drive.

213
00:15:27,050 --> 00:15:29,620
I drove quite a bit when I was
stationed in other cities for the news.

214
00:15:29,860 --> 00:15:30,960
Is that right?

215
00:15:33,730 --> 00:15:34,730
Why?

216
00:15:36,600 --> 00:15:39,800
Nothing. It's just really cool
to see you drive.

217
00:15:40,270 --> 00:15:41,370
It feels new.

218
00:15:41,970 --> 00:15:43,200
Says you.

219
00:15:46,110 --> 00:15:48,240
This is fun. I haven't driven in a while.

220
00:15:49,340 --> 00:15:51,680
I can't believe that I'm driving
a sports car.

221
00:15:52,810 --> 00:15:56,450
Da-jung, I think you should slow down.

222
00:15:56,650 --> 00:15:57,980
Da-jung!

223
00:15:58,050 --> 00:15:59,990
Da-jung!

224
00:16:03,720 --> 00:16:05,530
This place is beautiful.

225
00:16:06,330 --> 00:16:07,960
How did you find out about this place?

226
00:16:08,500 --> 00:16:10,260
- Do you like it?
- Yes.

227
00:16:11,300 --> 00:16:13,170
It's beautiful,

228
00:16:13,330 --> 00:16:15,070
and the air is fresh.

229
00:16:15,740 --> 00:16:16,770
I love it.

230
00:16:17,100 --> 00:16:20,340
That's good. I searched online
all night to find the place.

231
00:16:20,410 --> 00:16:22,040
- Really?
- Yes.

232
00:16:30,680 --> 00:16:32,490
- What?
- Get excited.

233
00:16:32,620 --> 00:16:34,790
We have a full-on date today.

234
00:16:44,160 --> 00:16:46,030
Stand over there.

235
00:16:52,030 --> 00:16:53,670
One, two, three.

236
00:16:58,610 --> 00:16:59,610
You look beautiful.

237
00:17:00,040 --> 00:17:01,540
Look at that!

238
00:17:02,270 --> 00:17:03,270
It's so pretty.

239
00:17:05,490 --> 00:17:06,540
Would I look good here?

240
00:17:07,950 --> 00:17:09,260
Here I go.

241
00:17:09,310 --> 00:17:11,050
One, two, three.

242
00:17:14,730 --> 00:17:16,760
Da-jung, stand over there.

243
00:17:18,060 --> 00:17:20,600
Give it to me. I'll take one of you now.

244
00:17:20,970 --> 00:17:21,900
I'm fine.

245
00:17:21,970 --> 00:17:24,140
Come on. We've come so far.

246
00:17:24,200 --> 00:17:26,270
We need a photo of you.

247
00:17:26,970 --> 00:17:29,340
Let's take one together then.

248
00:17:30,140 --> 00:17:31,140
Together?

249
00:17:34,110 --> 00:17:35,950
Here we go.

250
00:17:36,020 --> 00:17:38,150
One, two, three.

251
00:17:55,170 --> 00:17:57,670
It's been a while since we did this.
It's so much fun.

252
00:17:58,710 --> 00:18:00,970
We took photos on our first date too.

253
00:18:01,640 --> 00:18:03,640
We had a great time
at the Gyeongbokgung Palace, remember?

254
00:18:04,540 --> 00:18:05,710
You remember that?

255
00:18:05,780 --> 00:18:07,010
Absolutely.

256
00:18:07,310 --> 00:18:08,920
It was my first date with my first love.

257
00:18:08,980 --> 00:18:10,120
How can I forget that?

258
00:18:12,450 --> 00:18:15,890
I heard that I'm not
your first love though.

259
00:18:18,190 --> 00:18:20,530
What? Who said that?

260
00:18:20,790 --> 00:18:23,760
I heard Si-a say that at school.

261
00:18:26,230 --> 00:18:27,570
I see.

262
00:18:30,370 --> 00:18:33,440
How did I think that I was
your first love all along?

263
00:18:36,740 --> 00:18:37,840
Who on earth is it?

264
00:18:39,050 --> 00:18:41,850
Come on. It's all in the past now.

265
00:18:41,920 --> 00:18:43,920
First love doesn't mean anything.

266
00:18:43,980 --> 00:18:45,420
It means everything to me!

267
00:18:46,250 --> 00:18:47,250
Look at you.

268
00:18:47,820 --> 00:18:49,160
Why can't you say anything?

269
00:18:50,090 --> 00:18:51,190
Is it

270
00:18:51,860 --> 00:18:53,260
someone I know?

271
00:18:54,030 --> 00:18:55,030
What are you doing?

272
00:18:55,330 --> 00:18:57,930
Are you being jealous right now?

273
00:18:58,000 --> 00:18:59,370
Of course I am!

274
00:18:59,630 --> 00:19:00,630
What?

275
00:19:03,270 --> 00:19:04,300
All right.

276
00:19:05,840 --> 00:19:07,470
My first love is...

277
00:19:17,750 --> 00:19:19,650
Look! The sun is setting.

278
00:19:19,950 --> 00:19:22,160
That's too bad,
I want some more time here.

279
00:19:22,460 --> 00:19:23,890
Why aren't you saying anything?

280
00:19:24,720 --> 00:19:25,960
Tell me!

281
00:19:26,690 --> 00:19:28,560
Who is it?

282
00:19:29,200 --> 00:19:31,260
(If you're watching with your engine off,
turn it on every half an hour.)

283
00:19:42,040 --> 00:19:43,040
Here.

284
00:19:52,890 --> 00:19:53,890
Why are you smiling?

285
00:19:55,220 --> 00:19:56,260
Nothing.

286
00:19:56,890 --> 00:19:58,290
Coming to a movie theater

287
00:19:58,990 --> 00:20:01,060
just reminded me of the time
you got mad at me.

288
00:20:01,360 --> 00:20:02,360
At you?

289
00:20:03,330 --> 00:20:04,330
Why?

290
00:20:05,270 --> 00:20:06,670
You got really mad at me

291
00:20:07,570 --> 00:20:11,240
because I watched a movie
with Choi Il-kwon.

292
00:20:14,210 --> 00:20:16,410
To make you stop being mad, I...

293
00:20:19,750 --> 00:20:20,750
You what?

294
00:20:21,650 --> 00:20:22,650
What?

295
00:20:22,980 --> 00:20:24,450
What did you say?

296
00:20:25,080 --> 00:20:26,090
Well...

297
00:20:28,250 --> 00:20:29,620
I...

298
00:20:29,790 --> 00:20:30,760
"I love you."

299
00:20:32,990 --> 00:20:35,360
- What?
- That's what you said.

300
00:20:38,130 --> 00:20:39,130
Right.

301
00:20:46,210 --> 00:20:47,210
What?

302
00:20:47,310 --> 00:20:48,310
Nothing.

303
00:20:57,450 --> 00:20:59,290
(You're acting like it's your first relationship.)

304
00:20:59,350 --> 00:21:00,890
(I've had enough.)

305
00:21:04,090 --> 00:21:06,030
(The more time goes by,
the more confused I get.)

306
00:21:06,990 --> 00:21:09,230
(Now, I can tell what someone is like)

307
00:21:09,300 --> 00:21:11,330
(just after exchanging a few words.)

308
00:21:11,730 --> 00:21:12,970
(I understand why people say)

309
00:21:13,030 --> 00:21:15,470
(that you should date and get married
while you're still naive.)

310
00:21:16,300 --> 00:21:18,340
(You've never sincerely loved someone,
have you?)

311
00:21:19,640 --> 00:21:22,340
(I just don't fantasize about love.)

312
00:21:22,510 --> 00:21:24,410
(The old sayings are right.)

313
00:21:24,710 --> 00:21:27,150
(The more men you date, the better.)

314
00:21:27,210 --> 00:21:29,480
(All men are the same.)

315
00:21:54,840 --> 00:21:57,080
This is Si-a's favorite. Try some.

316
00:21:57,240 --> 00:21:58,240
Is that right?

317
00:22:04,880 --> 00:22:05,890
It's good.

318
00:22:06,490 --> 00:22:07,490
Is it?

319
00:22:07,690 --> 00:22:08,690
Yes.

320
00:22:17,660 --> 00:22:19,630
How long has it been since we last had
a date like this?

321
00:22:21,630 --> 00:22:22,640
I don't know.

322
00:22:23,770 --> 00:22:26,410
It's been so long, I don't even remember.

323
00:22:28,880 --> 00:22:31,640
I guess we've been so busy with our lives.

324
00:22:32,650 --> 00:22:33,710
I guess so.

325
00:22:34,050 --> 00:22:36,450
But it's not all bad.

326
00:22:36,520 --> 00:22:39,690
Since we haven't done a lot of things,
it's easier to get excited for them.

327
00:22:41,820 --> 00:22:45,530
Then, let's do all the things
we didn't get to do when we were young.

328
00:22:45,860 --> 00:22:46,860
Sure.

329
00:23:00,140 --> 00:23:01,540
Isn't that Jung Da-jung?

330
00:23:02,240 --> 00:23:04,410
Yes, I think it is her.

331
00:23:04,810 --> 00:23:07,110
- Who is that guy next to her?
- Right?

332
00:23:14,890 --> 00:23:16,020
Aren't you

333
00:23:16,460 --> 00:23:18,690
Ms. Jung Da-jung, the anchorwoman?

334
00:23:20,960 --> 00:23:22,660
Yes.

335
00:23:23,500 --> 00:23:25,300
I'm a fan.

336
00:23:26,600 --> 00:23:28,630
I heard you had a son in high school.

337
00:23:29,570 --> 00:23:32,770
My gosh. You and your son
must be very close.

338
00:23:33,670 --> 00:23:36,940
- I see. It's her son.
- No wonder.

339
00:23:38,440 --> 00:23:39,450
Yes.

340
00:23:40,180 --> 00:23:41,350
Thank you.

341
00:23:41,410 --> 00:23:43,280
Okay. Enjoy your sandwich.

342
00:24:09,510 --> 00:24:10,710
You must be tired.

343
00:24:11,180 --> 00:24:12,210
Not at all.

344
00:24:12,710 --> 00:24:15,210
I had a lot of fun today.

345
00:24:25,090 --> 00:24:26,860
What if someone sees us?

346
00:24:29,460 --> 00:24:32,200
- I'm sorry.
- I'll go inside.

347
00:24:33,270 --> 00:24:34,330
Okay.

348
00:25:44,800 --> 00:25:46,670
I really hate him.

349
00:25:50,210 --> 00:25:53,010
(He likes you. And)

350
00:25:53,380 --> 00:25:54,950
you like him too.

351
00:25:59,390 --> 00:26:00,790
What are you two doing?

352
00:26:02,490 --> 00:26:03,490
Yes.

353
00:26:04,320 --> 00:26:05,930
I'm dating Ji-ho.

354
00:26:06,990 --> 00:26:07,990
What?

355
00:26:12,370 --> 00:26:15,270
Can you keep this a secret
to other people?

356
00:26:15,330 --> 00:26:16,440
Okay?

357
00:26:18,000 --> 00:26:21,210
So you two are really dating?

358
00:26:21,570 --> 00:26:22,510
Yes.

359
00:26:23,240 --> 00:26:24,980
You're the only one who knows.

360
00:26:25,480 --> 00:26:26,750
We're friends.

361
00:26:29,050 --> 00:26:32,590
Okay. I'm your friend. Right.

362
00:26:33,020 --> 00:26:34,620
You'll keep our secret, right?

363
00:26:36,760 --> 00:26:39,260
Then, we'll get going.

364
00:26:59,350 --> 00:27:00,380
Hello?

365
00:27:00,450 --> 00:27:02,280
(I'm calling from Serim High School.)

366
00:27:02,450 --> 00:27:05,550
(Is this Mr. Hong Dae-young, Hong Si-a's father?)

367
00:27:05,620 --> 00:27:07,350
Yes, this is him.

368
00:27:07,890 --> 00:27:09,090
What is this about?

369
00:27:11,260 --> 00:27:12,360
Hello?

370
00:27:13,460 --> 00:27:14,730
Go ahead.

371
00:27:17,630 --> 00:27:18,730
What was that?

372
00:27:23,440 --> 00:27:26,810
This is Woo-young's phone number.

373
00:28:02,280 --> 00:28:03,640
Gosh.

374
00:28:04,810 --> 00:28:05,810
I know

375
00:28:07,250 --> 00:28:09,280
you explained this to me,
but this is hard to believe.

376
00:28:14,720 --> 00:28:16,520
Even you found out, Ji-ho.

377
00:28:17,860 --> 00:28:19,230
I'm sorry about this.

378
00:28:20,560 --> 00:28:21,930
Don't say that.

379
00:28:22,400 --> 00:28:23,630
I'm sorry.

380
00:28:24,400 --> 00:28:26,400
I had no idea who you were
and was rude to you.

381
00:28:26,470 --> 00:28:29,500
No. You were never rude to me.

382
00:28:32,970 --> 00:28:34,140
I'm sorry.

383
00:28:34,440 --> 00:28:37,080
No. Gosh. Sit down.

384
00:28:44,450 --> 00:28:45,620
But Ji-ho,

385
00:28:46,620 --> 00:28:48,020
how did you figure it out?

386
00:28:49,060 --> 00:28:50,120
Well,

387
00:28:50,820 --> 00:28:54,190
I have a video of the sports day
at my elementary school.

388
00:28:54,460 --> 00:28:56,460
I remembered the video and watched it.

389
00:28:57,160 --> 00:28:58,630
And your face...

390
00:28:58,700 --> 00:28:59,900
I see.

391
00:29:02,170 --> 00:29:04,040
I still wasn't sure then,

392
00:29:04,200 --> 00:29:06,440
but I saw you two hugging each other.

393
00:29:09,340 --> 00:29:11,980
I was able to stop Si-a from seeing that.

394
00:29:12,410 --> 00:29:14,310
But she almost caught you.

395
00:29:18,820 --> 00:29:20,020
But Ji-ho,

396
00:29:20,950 --> 00:29:24,460
that means you were on a date
with my daughter until now.

397
00:29:26,160 --> 00:29:27,190
Well,

398
00:29:27,890 --> 00:29:30,800
today was our first date.

399
00:29:30,860 --> 00:29:32,300
Is that so?

400
00:29:35,700 --> 00:29:37,400
Tell me if you need more allowance.

401
00:29:38,440 --> 00:29:41,310
I'll give you some money
for keeping my secret.

402
00:29:43,340 --> 00:29:44,340
Thank you.

403
00:29:50,120 --> 00:29:51,080
Gosh.

404
00:29:51,720 --> 00:29:53,520
Mr. Hong.

405
00:29:53,590 --> 00:29:54,990
Yes? What is it?

406
00:29:58,420 --> 00:30:00,630
Coming back to your old self

407
00:30:01,360 --> 00:30:02,800
will be hard, right?

408
00:30:13,640 --> 00:30:16,180
- Wasn't that really delicious?
- You were eating a lot.

409
00:30:19,150 --> 00:30:20,250
Si-a.

410
00:30:20,780 --> 00:30:22,450
Let's walk around your house
one more time.

411
00:30:22,720 --> 00:30:25,650
- Why?
- I don't want to say goodbye yet.

412
00:30:27,590 --> 00:30:28,720
Okay.

413
00:30:31,090 --> 00:30:32,320
It was so good.

414
00:30:33,860 --> 00:30:36,330
Dad, aren't you tired?
I'll give you a massage at home.

415
00:30:36,400 --> 00:30:37,960
Thanks, my princess.

416
00:30:38,830 --> 00:30:39,930
When I get home...

417
00:30:40,000 --> 00:30:41,970
- What is it?
- Okay?

418
00:30:42,030 --> 00:30:43,400
They seem happy together.

419
00:30:43,700 --> 00:30:46,110
I was always mean to my dad.

420
00:30:50,110 --> 00:30:52,910
When he called, I didn't answer it
because it was a hassle.

421
00:30:52,980 --> 00:30:54,980
Whenever we were together, I was grumpy.

422
00:30:55,820 --> 00:30:57,720
When he bought me a meal the other day,

423
00:30:57,780 --> 00:31:00,550
I invited my friends
because I didn't want him to nag me.

424
00:31:02,790 --> 00:31:05,290
Had I known it would be this hard
to see my dad again,

425
00:31:05,360 --> 00:31:06,930
I would have been nicer to him.

426
00:31:19,270 --> 00:31:20,440
Si-a

427
00:31:22,640 --> 00:31:24,410
is waiting for you.

428
00:31:52,710 --> 00:31:54,440
Why is she calling me?

429
00:31:58,110 --> 00:31:59,980
Hey, what is it?

430
00:32:02,410 --> 00:32:05,420
What? The police station?

431
00:32:06,550 --> 00:32:10,420
Are you sure this is it?
Don't you have more?

432
00:32:10,490 --> 00:32:11,760
No. That's it.

433
00:32:11,820 --> 00:32:13,490
You should come clean now.

434
00:32:13,490 --> 00:32:15,090
(Human Rights, Justice, and Kindness)

435
00:32:15,330 --> 00:32:17,460
I told you I don't have it.

436
00:32:17,460 --> 00:32:18,500
(Police, Trustworthy Police)

437
00:32:18,930 --> 00:32:22,170
I'm Lawyer Chu Ae-rin of Taebaek Law Firm.
What is this about?

438
00:32:22,230 --> 00:32:24,870
Ae-rin! I'm being wrongfully accused.

439
00:32:25,440 --> 00:32:28,140
She has been constantly leaving
malicious comments

440
00:32:28,210 --> 00:32:30,140
to those who do one-person broadcasts.

441
00:32:30,310 --> 00:32:32,610
They came together to sue her.

442
00:32:33,650 --> 00:32:34,710
Malicious comments?

443
00:32:35,210 --> 00:32:36,880
I didn't write them for that purpose.

444
00:32:36,950 --> 00:32:39,080
They feel guilty which is why they're overreacting.

445
00:32:40,120 --> 00:32:41,990
Please help me.

446
00:32:42,920 --> 00:32:45,020
Can I see the complaint and evidence?

447
00:32:45,090 --> 00:32:46,090
Okay.

448
00:32:47,590 --> 00:32:48,690
Here.

449
00:32:49,760 --> 00:32:52,330
(Black Nail's Comment List)

450
00:32:53,930 --> 00:32:56,500
- She wrote this much?
- They were really upset.

451
00:32:56,570 --> 00:32:58,940
They looked up her nickname and IP address

452
00:32:59,000 --> 00:33:00,570
and collected everything she wrote.

453
00:33:07,150 --> 00:33:08,880
(You're overreacting again. I'm sick of it.)

454
00:33:08,950 --> 00:33:11,850
(I went to high school with Jung Da-jung,)

455
00:33:11,920 --> 00:33:15,120
(and she got pregnant in high school.)

456
00:33:19,190 --> 00:33:20,930
- What is this?
- What?

457
00:33:23,660 --> 00:33:25,100
This?

458
00:33:25,560 --> 00:33:28,900
You were always really mean to Da-jung ever
since we were young.

459
00:33:29,230 --> 00:33:30,770
What's your problem with her?

460
00:33:31,200 --> 00:33:34,510
Gosh. I've always hated Jung Da-jung.

461
00:33:34,570 --> 00:33:37,540
Also, before Jung Da-jung appeared,

462
00:33:37,610 --> 00:33:39,350
you and I were best friends.

463
00:33:39,580 --> 00:33:42,620
If it wasn't for her,
you and I wouldn't have gotten so distant.

464
00:33:44,150 --> 00:33:46,620
When I saw she was having a hard time in life,

465
00:33:46,690 --> 00:33:50,020
I thought she was getting punished,
so I tried to forgive her.

466
00:33:50,520 --> 00:33:52,560
But she became an anchorwoman and appeared on TV

467
00:33:52,560 --> 00:33:54,030
and acted like she was so nice and smart.

468
00:33:54,080 --> 00:33:56,120
I couldn't hold it in when I saw her acting so fake.

469
00:33:56,390 --> 00:33:58,730
I wanted everyone to find out what a greedy

470
00:33:58,800 --> 00:34:00,120
and selfish person she is.

471
00:34:03,070 --> 00:34:06,210
I think the term selfish suits you more.

472
00:34:06,370 --> 00:34:07,770
- What?
- You know,

473
00:34:07,830 --> 00:34:09,740
I have a belief when I defend someone.

474
00:34:09,810 --> 00:34:12,210
I try to embrace trashy people with my heart.

475
00:34:12,410 --> 00:34:16,080
But I can't embrace someone
who talks ill about my friend.

476
00:34:17,220 --> 00:34:19,080
You can look for another lawyer,

477
00:34:20,290 --> 00:34:21,490
or you can settle with them.

478
00:34:22,890 --> 00:34:25,160
Hey! Why do you only care for her?

479
00:34:25,220 --> 00:34:26,930
I'm your friend too, darn it!

480
00:34:32,330 --> 00:34:35,430
Do you remember when the girls
from the other school came looking for me?

481
00:34:35,500 --> 00:34:37,370
- I told you to behave.
- It's not that...

482
00:34:37,430 --> 00:34:39,200
You've gotten quite bold, haven't you?

483
00:34:39,270 --> 00:34:40,600
- Let go of it.
- Sang-Hee.

484
00:34:40,660 --> 00:34:42,310
- Hey.
- What are you looking at?

485
00:34:42,370 --> 00:34:43,380
We're not done talking.

486
00:34:43,440 --> 00:34:45,540
- Do you think this is a joke?
- Please, stop.

487
00:34:46,610 --> 00:34:47,650
Back then...

488
00:34:47,710 --> 00:34:50,380
You can't call someone a friend
when they ignore you

489
00:34:50,450 --> 00:34:52,280
when you're in trouble.

490
00:34:52,920 --> 00:34:55,190
It's all in the past anyway.

491
00:34:55,990 --> 00:34:58,420
Right. It's all in the past.

492
00:34:58,520 --> 00:34:59,690
What happened then

493
00:35:00,660 --> 00:35:01,660
and what's happening now.

494
00:35:02,060 --> 00:35:05,660
Don't go around and tell people
that we're friends.

495
00:35:05,900 --> 00:35:08,800
I'll sue you for spreading false information.

496
00:35:23,480 --> 00:35:24,780
Just wait and see.

497
00:35:30,790 --> 00:35:32,960
(KBF National Athletic Meet, Men's Basketball)
Okay. Quiet.

498
00:35:34,090 --> 00:35:35,430
Congratulations

499
00:35:35,830 --> 00:35:36,900
on winning the semi-finals.

500
00:35:41,500 --> 00:35:42,700
You guys should all get rest,

501
00:35:42,770 --> 00:35:44,540
- and I'll see you tomorrow at practice.
- Yes, sir.

502
00:35:44,600 --> 00:35:46,970
- Good job, you guys.
- Good job.

503
00:35:47,940 --> 00:35:49,780
Go Woo-young and Hong Si-woo.
See me for a second.

504
00:35:50,410 --> 00:35:51,410
Yes, sir.

505
00:35:52,380 --> 00:35:53,950
(Be in your best condition for the best outcome.)

506
00:35:54,050 --> 00:35:56,980
The scout for Hankuk University said
he was very impressed

507
00:35:57,380 --> 00:35:58,980
by the two of you.

508
00:36:02,350 --> 00:36:05,720
If we win the finals,
Hankuk University said they want to scout you two.

509
00:36:05,960 --> 00:36:06,960
So do your best.

510
00:36:07,030 --> 00:36:08,030
Yes, sir.

511
00:36:08,290 --> 00:36:10,030
- Yes, sir.
- Good job.

512
00:36:10,500 --> 00:36:11,830
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

513
00:36:14,270 --> 00:36:16,640
Hey. Nice.

514
00:36:16,700 --> 00:36:17,700
Good job.

515
00:36:17,940 --> 00:36:20,570
Isn't Hankuk University
the school you wanted to go to?

516
00:36:20,640 --> 00:36:21,970
This is great, Si-woo.

517
00:36:22,610 --> 00:36:24,340
Let's go to Hankuk University together.

518
00:36:26,510 --> 00:36:27,510
Right.

519
00:36:32,120 --> 00:36:33,820
Woo-young. You should go first.

520
00:36:33,890 --> 00:36:35,220
I'm going to make a phone call.

521
00:36:35,320 --> 00:36:36,490
Oh, okay.

522
00:36:36,560 --> 00:36:37,560
Okay.

523
00:36:51,170 --> 00:36:53,140
(My Son)

524
00:37:08,350 --> 00:37:09,490
Hey, Si-woo.

525
00:37:10,190 --> 00:37:13,560
Hi, Dad. The finals are next Saturday.
Can you come?

526
00:37:16,360 --> 00:37:18,360
I want to go, but...

527
00:37:18,430 --> 00:37:19,530
(Oh, right.)

528
00:37:19,970 --> 00:37:21,400
You're busy these days, right?

529
00:37:23,870 --> 00:37:25,600
It's okay if you can't come.

530
00:37:26,710 --> 00:37:27,710
I'll hang up now.

531
00:37:41,250 --> 00:37:43,460
What? You didn't leave yet?

532
00:37:44,060 --> 00:37:46,020
No. I wanted to go with you.

533
00:37:46,160 --> 00:37:47,160
I see.

534
00:37:50,930 --> 00:37:53,700
You look really upset.

535
00:37:55,830 --> 00:37:57,040
To be honest,

536
00:38:00,210 --> 00:38:03,140
I became interested in basketball
because of my dad.

537
00:38:06,210 --> 00:38:08,350
Is that so?

538
00:38:09,110 --> 00:38:10,120
Yes.

539
00:38:11,580 --> 00:38:12,620
My dad

540
00:38:13,550 --> 00:38:15,490
was Serim High School basketball team's ace,

541
00:38:16,290 --> 00:38:19,490
but after I was born, he quit playing.

542
00:38:20,660 --> 00:38:23,600
That's why
I wanted to achieve my dad's dream for him.

543
00:38:24,700 --> 00:38:27,130
But I was afraid he'd be disappointed if I was bad,

544
00:38:28,530 --> 00:38:30,770
so I pretended not to care about basketball.

545
00:38:34,270 --> 00:38:36,840
I didn't know you had those thoughts.

546
00:38:39,650 --> 00:38:41,710
I wanted to tell him
when I was good enough.

547
00:38:44,650 --> 00:38:46,920
That's why
when I got into the basketball team,

548
00:38:46,990 --> 00:38:49,020
