00:59:25,140 --> 00:59:26,140
I will

818
00:59:27,080 --> 00:59:30,680
do whatever it takes
to find a way to go back.

819
00:59:33,350 --> 00:59:34,590
What about your dream?

820
00:59:35,590 --> 00:59:37,020
To me, you and our children

821
00:59:37,820 --> 00:59:39,560
are more important than my dream.

822
00:59:40,560 --> 00:59:41,630
So

823
00:59:42,490 --> 00:59:44,630
will you give up your dream
just like before?

824
00:59:45,760 --> 00:59:47,070
I'm not giving it up.

825
00:59:47,130 --> 00:59:48,130
Then, what is it?

826
00:59:49,430 --> 00:59:52,740
This is exactly why I was so anxious.

827
00:59:55,070 --> 00:59:56,070
Da-jung.

828
00:59:57,910 --> 01:00:00,240
I can't do this anymore. Let's

829
01:00:01,250 --> 01:00:02,650
really end this now.

830
01:00:08,850 --> 01:00:10,290
Don't say things you don't mean.

831
01:00:11,020 --> 01:00:12,020
No.

832
01:00:14,260 --> 01:00:15,690
I called you,

833
01:00:16,930 --> 01:00:18,230
so I can say this to you.

834
01:00:21,470 --> 01:00:24,570
Our kids are all grown up now.

835
01:00:25,570 --> 01:00:27,670
I can look after them by myself.

836
01:00:27,970 --> 01:00:31,280
So you should live your own life.

837
01:00:33,040 --> 01:00:34,710
You're a good person.

838
01:00:35,210 --> 01:00:37,250
And you deserve more than that.

839
01:00:39,120 --> 01:00:40,220
Da-jung.

840
01:00:42,350 --> 01:00:43,860
You can stay

841
01:00:45,320 --> 01:00:46,560
in their lives

842
01:00:48,890 --> 01:00:50,360
as their friend just like now.

843
01:00:51,930 --> 01:00:53,160
And we should

844
01:00:57,200 --> 01:00:58,870
live our own lives.

845
01:01:02,270 --> 01:01:03,780
Da-jung.

846
01:01:09,480 --> 01:01:10,620
I...

847
01:01:12,650 --> 01:01:15,250
I want to stay by your side.

848
01:01:16,290 --> 01:01:18,760
Look what happened to your life
when you did that.

849
01:01:22,460 --> 01:01:23,530
To be honest,

850
01:01:25,900 --> 01:01:27,270
it was

851
01:01:28,630 --> 01:01:30,470
really hard seeing you

852
01:01:32,700 --> 01:01:34,070
play basketball.

853
01:01:35,170 --> 01:01:36,710
(You seemed so happy)

854
01:01:37,440 --> 01:01:39,240
(when you were playing basketball.)

855
01:01:41,250 --> 01:01:43,010
(It made me wonder)

856
01:01:43,880 --> 01:01:45,250
(what would have happened)

857
01:01:46,180 --> 01:01:48,450
(if I didn't tell you I was pregnant
18 years ago.)

858
01:01:53,160 --> 01:01:55,130
I kept thinking about that in my head

859
01:01:56,830 --> 01:01:58,000
and regretted it.

860
01:02:01,130 --> 01:02:02,630
You did too,

861
01:02:03,670 --> 01:02:04,700
didn't you?

862
01:02:14,450 --> 01:02:16,350
Regretting your life with me once

863
01:02:17,450 --> 01:02:18,750
is enough.

864
01:02:20,720 --> 01:02:22,250
We know it firsthand.

865
01:02:23,690 --> 01:02:24,990
I won't do that again.

866
01:02:31,500 --> 01:02:32,900
Give me a chance.

867
01:02:35,430 --> 01:02:36,500
No.

868
01:02:41,340 --> 01:02:43,310
You already have a chance now.

869
01:02:44,110 --> 01:02:45,280
Don't

870
01:02:46,710 --> 01:02:47,910
miss that chance.

871
01:02:50,620 --> 01:02:51,720
Woo-young.

872
01:03:39,000 --> 01:03:42,330
(Passion, pride, and Serim)

873
01:03:47,470 --> 01:03:48,740
Let's go back,

874
01:03:49,770 --> 01:03:50,980
Hong Dae-young.

875
01:03:59,680 --> 01:04:00,720
Gosh.

876
01:04:15,130 --> 01:04:16,270
Please.

877
01:04:17,770 --> 01:04:20,100
Please. Let's go back to my real life.

878
01:04:41,090 --> 01:04:43,130
I want my life back!

879
01:04:50,230 --> 01:04:54,010
Why can't I go back? Why not?

880
01:04:55,710 --> 01:04:59,540
Please!

881
01:05:35,150 --> 01:05:37,350
(Epilogue)

882
01:05:37,420 --> 01:05:39,420
(We are Korea!)

883
01:05:45,090 --> 01:05:46,190
Yes, Mom.

884
01:05:47,090 --> 01:05:50,330
What's wrong with your voice?
Did something happen?

885
01:05:52,560 --> 01:05:54,470
No. Nothing happened.

886
01:05:56,300 --> 01:05:57,570
Da-jung.

887
01:05:58,400 --> 01:06:00,570
Move back home with your kids
if it's too hard.

888
01:06:04,480 --> 01:06:07,610
No. Dae-young takes good care of us.

889
01:06:08,450 --> 01:06:09,710
I'm all right.

890
01:06:10,410 --> 01:06:10,750
(Deoksan Hill)

891
01:06:10,750 --> 01:06:14,090
- Let's go, Korea!
- Let's go, Korea!

892
01:06:19,890 --> 01:06:23,060
(Everyone was wildly cheering for Korea
in summer of 2002.)

893
01:06:23,960 --> 01:06:27,630
(You at the age of 20 cried
because you were heartbroken)

894
01:06:29,370 --> 01:06:30,940
(by your own misery)

895
01:06:31,640 --> 01:06:33,370
(and by heartless people.)

896
01:06:34,140 --> 01:06:35,610
(They made you cry.)

897
01:06:36,910 --> 01:06:38,440
(I wanted to comfort you)

898
01:06:39,040 --> 01:06:42,110
(by telling you not to try so hard
when you were crying.)

899
01:06:42,880 --> 01:06:43,980
Da-jung.

900
01:06:51,190 --> 01:06:53,860
(But you tried
and put a smile on your face.)

901
01:06:55,730 --> 01:06:58,030
Why did you wait for me out here?
You must be tired.

902
01:06:58,430 --> 01:07:01,670
(And I didn't want to make you cry.)

903
01:07:11,010 --> 01:07:12,180
Are you okay?

904
01:07:12,880 --> 01:07:15,280
Oh, this? I'm fine.

905
01:07:15,950 --> 01:07:17,310
It's a small cut.

906
01:07:18,520 --> 01:07:21,220
(When the whole world
turned its back on you,)

907
01:07:23,090 --> 01:07:25,690
(I believed in you.)

908
01:07:26,990 --> 01:07:29,330
(We were covered in wounds.)

909
01:07:30,560 --> 01:07:31,830
(But)

910
01:07:33,500 --> 01:07:36,030
(we were each other's brightest star.)
